node.title: Warren Buffet's Top Tips for Investing in the Stock Market

node.text: Financial Literacy is the MOST important part when it comes to building wealth. Those who don't understand how to manage money usually don't hold onto it for long.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Market Hustle 👨‍💻 in New York, New York with @biz.of.wealth. May be an image of text that says 'Business of Wealth @bizofwealth Trying to get rich in a couple of weeks is what will stop you from getting rich in a couple of years.'.

node.text: Start thinking in 10 year terms, not 10 day terms!

node.accessibility_caption: Stocks

node.text:
60%!! 

It’s not what you make, but HOW you manage what you make that matters. 

Making $100k and spending $100k = BROKE. 

Spend less than you make and invest the rest! 💯🔥

node.text: Don’t ever think it’s too late to start something new or make a change. Toss your timeline out the window and just take action!

node.text: Wealth is built by INVESTING in income producing assets! 💯🔥

Stocks

node.text: The less you check your portfolio, the less likely you’ll make an irrational investing decision. Keep your focus on the long term, not what’s going on in the short term! 💯🔥

node.accessibility_caption: Stocks

node.text:
Self discipline is sticking to your investment strategy when your emotions are screaming at you to do the wrong thing. 

Self discipline is important in almost every area of life, especially when it comes to making money!

Practice makes perfect. Start by mastering the little things.

Yes you need a place to live, but you DON'T need a place that costs 3/4 of your income. Yes you need to eat, but you DON'T need to spend $250 per week on eating out. Live modestly and build wealth'.

node.text: You build wealth by living below your means. The more money you have left over after covering all of your expenses, the more you can invest and faster you can build wealth. 🔥💯

node.text:
Don’t underestimate the small contributions when you’re saving up for an emergency fund, vacation fund, etc. 

The small contributions add up quickly!

Saving $25 per week is $1,300 per year, which is plenty for a nice vacation. 💯🔥

node.accessibility_caption: Stocks

node.text: “You don't need to be a rocket scientist. Investing is not a game where the guy with the 160 IQ beats the guy with the 130 IQ.” - Warren Buffett

node.accessibility_caption: Stocks

node.text: Every dollar invested is another dollar closer to financial freedom 💯🔥
